As a guest paying invoice through PWK (Mobile browser), I should have the ability to scan QR code of physical SD card. This is efficient approach because almost users that want to pay invoice do not have Kanoo Account to proceed to pay.

*Acceptance Criteria*

* While using PWK to pay the invoice, the third payment method The SandDollar Card will have a change. Clicking on it display two sub-tabs
* Reference app: This is the default tab. This is to use reference app to scan the QR code. This should work as current. 
* Physical SD card: Selecting this displays the scanner to scan SEND side of physical SD card. 
** If I scan a QR code that does NOT contain {{nzia:sqr}}, it displays red message below the scanner {color:#00b8d9}_“This code is invalid“_{color}
** If QR code contains {{nzia:sqr}}, I move to Confirm screen where I see the total amount again and have to enter Sand Dollar PIN. 
*** Continue button is only enabled when I enter fully 6 digits
*** Clicking on Continue button does not validate anything. It navigates to the next screen to enter Sand Dollar OTP. 
** Enter Sand Dollar OTP screen: 
*** Make Payment button is only enabled when I enter fully 6 digits
** Clicking on Make Payment button will move to Failed Payment or Successful Payment screen
*** Failed Payment: I will move to this screen if I can not pass 
**** If PIN is incorrect, display message {color:#00b8d9}_“PIN is invalid. Please try again\!“_{color}
**** If OTP is incorrect, display message {color:#00b8d9}_“OTP is invalid. Please try again\!“_{color}
**** If QR code is incorrect, display message {color:#00b8d9}_“This code is invalid. Please try again\!“_{color} Validating this is to ensure the QR code is completely correct.
**** If my SD card does not have enough money, display message {color:#00b8d9}_“The transaction failed because of insufficient balance in your card.“_{color}
** If there is no problem, clicking on Make Payment button complete the payment
** There is Back button to be back to the PIN enter screen
** Every time I move to another tab then am back to Physical SD card, it should display the scanner again


