*NOTING FOR DEVELOPER ABOUT CONNECTION POOL* on {color:#ff5630}VisipayService{color}.

To solve trouble with {color:#ff5630}running out of Connection Pool{color} in SpingBoot on VisipayService. 

# {color:#ff5630}We disabled "Open Session In View"{color} (OSIV) on VisipayService by config:
{color:#00b8d9}spring.jpa.open-in-view=false{color}
# So, {color:#ff5630}DO NOT use LazyLoading  on VisipayService{color} (a LazyInitializationException may be thrown when you fetch a lazy-loaded property).
{color:#00b8d9}@OneToMany{color}: default LAZY loading.
{color:#00b8d9}@ManyToMany{color}: default LAZY loading.
Example: {color:#ff5630}Entity using LazyLoading{color}
{code:java}@Data
@Entity
@Table(name = "users")
public class User implements Serializable {
  @Id
  @Column(name = "user_id")
  private Integer userId;

  @Column(name = "first_name")
  private String firstName;

  @Column(name = "last_name")
  private String lastName;

  @Column(name = "user_name")
  private String userName;

  @ManyToMany(fetch = FetchType.LAZY)
  @EqualsAndHashCode.Exclude
  @ToString.Exclude
  @JoinTable(name = "users_roles", joinColumns = @JoinColumn(name = "user_id"), inverseJoinColumns = @JoinColumn(name = "role_id"))
  private Collection<Role> roles;

  @ManyToMany(fetch = FetchType.LAZY)
  @EqualsAndHashCode.Exclude
  @ToString.Exclude
  @JoinTable(name = "agency_users", joinColumns = @JoinColumn(name = "user_id"), inverseJoinColumns = @JoinColumn(name = "agency_id"))
  private Collection<Agency> agencies;
}{code}

{color:#36b37e}LazyInitializationException{color} will be thrown at {color:#ff5630}line 10{color} when call {color:#ff5630}user.getRoles();{color}
{code:java}public class CustomUserDetails implements UserDetails {
  @Getter
  private final User user;

  public CustomUserDetails(User user) {
      this.user = user;
  }
  @Override
  public Collection<? extends GrantedAuthority> getAuthorities() {
      Collection<Role> roles = this.user.getRoles();
      return roles.stream().map(role -> new SimpleGrantedAuthority(role.getCode())).collect(Collectors.toList());
  }
}{code}
# {color:#ff5630}The best option{color} for that is to {color:#ff5630}load the entity with all required associations in one query{color}. Or you can use a {color:#ff5630}DTO projection{color}, which doesn’t support lazy loading and needs to be fully initialized before you return it to the client.
# About using FETCH JOIN, DTO projection, … see this guide: [https://thorben-janssen.com/lazyinitializationexception/#:~:text=Hibernate%20throws%20the%20LazyInitializationException%20when,client%20application%20or%20web%20layer.|https://thorben-janssen.com/lazyinitializationexception/#:~:text=Hibernate%20throws%20the%20LazyInitializationException%20when,client%20application%20or%20web%20layer.|smart-link]

